HEADWORD: Bletonism
<hw>Ble"ton*ism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The supposed
faculty of perceiving subterraneous springs and currents by sensation;
-- so called from one <xex>Bleton</xex>, of France.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

